<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-08T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8891:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-08T14:00:00+03:00">March
                                        8, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received March 8—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>453. I have learned from a non-British source which I regard as
                                reliable that prior to his departure for Ankara<note n="11" xml:id="d170fn11">Sir Stafford Cripps left Moscow on February
                                    26, 1941.</note> to meet Eden, the British Ambassador informally
                                suggested to the Soviet authorities that Eden might be prepared to
                                visit Moscow, but that they did not encourage the visit.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>